		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: plus / moins / aussi … que",
		"body": "Compare with **plus … que** (more … than), **moins … que** (less … than), **aussi … que** (as … as): *Les mangues sont plus chères que les pommes.* The adjective still agrees (chère/chères). Hindi uses से ज़्यादा / से कम (… than) — same idea, different position. For quantities use **de**: *un kilo **de** légumes*, *beaucoup **de** thé*.",
